MOGWASE – The North West High Court sitting in Mogwase outside Rustenburg on Tuesday dismissed murder charges against Marikana activist and Forum 4 Service Delivery councillor Napoleon Webster, and five other men. Judge Ronnie Hendricks ruled that there was no evidence against them. "The following order is made: your application is granted, you are not found guilty and discharged." READ: Marikana men drank blood of their victim, NW High Court hears The case relates to the murder of Sanco member, Sabata Petros Chale, who was hacked to death on December 8, 2016, in Marikana West, allegedly by Aubrey Seitsang, Sibonile Sobopha, Mdlondozi Fundiwo, Herbert Baqhesi, Webster, William Nyenyane, Aphindile Pungone, Samson Gqwetani, Gift Luveli, Nkululeko Msithwa, Nkosindiphile Nziyose, Luvo Soyizwaphi, Sivuyile Qasha and Mzolisi Mbulana. The court heard the accused drank Chale's blood. The State conceded on Monday that there was not enough evidence against Fundiwo, Webster, Pungone, Luveli, Msithwa and Soyizwaphi. African News Agency